text: Stéphane Lambese (born 10 May 1995) is a Haitianhttp://www.lestitisdupsg.fr/sel-haiti-une-premiere-reussie-pour- stephane-lambese/ professional footballer who plays as a right back for US Orléans. ==Club career== Born in Nogent-sur-Marne, France, Lambese began his career in 2004 with Olympique de Sevran,Sevran - Stéphane Lambese un Sevranais au PSG before moving in the summer of 2009 to the youth of Paris Saint- Germain.Paris Saint-Germain official website - Stéphane Lambese In the summer of 2012, he moved from the youth in the reserveReserve Paris SG Statistiques des Joueurs Foot CFA 2012/2013 of PSG and had his senior debut against the reserve of AS Nancy in the Championnat de France Amateur on 20 April 2013.Foot National - Stephane Lambese He moved on loan from FC Lorient to Stade Lavallois in July 2018. ==International career== Lambese represented 2010 in four international for the French U-16 football team.Fédération Française De Football - Stéphane Lambese Since 2014, he represents the national team of Haiti, he is part of the U-20 national team.Les Titis Du PSG - U20/haïti = Stéphane Lambese Participe À La Ronde Caribéenne !!!
